-- PKN Orlen May Buy Remaining 15% of Anwil, Break Up Company, Parkiet Says
-- Monika Rozlal
-- 2010-07-12T05:30:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/pkn-orlen-may-buy-remaining-15-of-anwil-break-up-company-parkiet-says.html

          
          
             PKN Orlen SA  may buy the shares it
doesnâ€™t own in Anwil SA and break up and sell the company after
failing to obtain a satisfactory price in June for its 85
percent stake,  Parkiet  said.  
 Orlen may split the chemical maker into a fertilizer and
petrochemical unit and put them on sale separately next year,
the newspaper said, citing Deputy Chief Executive Officer
 Slawomir Jedrzejczyk .  
 Orlen would have to spend as much as 200 million zloty ($62
million) to buy the 15.2 percent of Anwil owned by minority
shareholders, including the government and Energa SA, Parkiet
said.  
